                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_cævæg" xml:lang="os"><form type="lemma"><orth>cævæg</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>коса (орудие)</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>scythe</q></tr></sense><exampleGrp><example><quote>jæxīcæn nyssaʒy ysqælfynʒ cævæg</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>налаживает себе косу со вздернутым концом</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>[he] sets up a scythe with an upturned end</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>56</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>cævægæj, ... æxsyrfæj cættæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>коса, ... серп наготове</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>scythe, ... reaping hook are ready</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>124</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><re><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>cævægqæd</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>cævægǧædæ</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>древко косы</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>shaft of the scythe</q></tr></sense><exampleGrp><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>sawdortæ cævæg insunmæ, cævægǧædtæ...</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>оселки („черные камни“) для точки косы, древка косы...</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>touchstones (‘black stones’) for wheting the scythe, shaft of the scythe</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_SD"/><biblScope>245%l3%l</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp></re><exampleGrp><example><quote>jæxīcæn nyssaʒy ysqælfynʒ cævæg</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>налаживает себе косу со вздернутым концом</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>[he] sets up a scythe with an upturned end</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>56</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>cævægæj, ... æxsyrfæj cættæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>коса, ... серп наготове</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>scythe, ... reaping hook are ready</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>124</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Лексикализованное причастие на -%iæg%i от глагола <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cævyn"/> ‘бить’, собственно „бьющее“ или „секущее“ орудие. Ср. по образованию <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/> <w>šalga</w> <gloss><q>коса</q></gloss></mentioned> %bшорск%b. , буквально „бьющее (орудие)“ от <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/> <w>šal-</w> <gloss><q>бить</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""><w/> <gloss><q>ударять</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (<bibl><author>Дыренкова</author><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Грамматика шорского языка, стр. 28</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">The grammar of Shor, p. 28</biblScope></bibl>); Развитие значения ‘бить’ → ‘косить’, как в немецком <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/> <w>hauen</w> <gloss><q>бить</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="de"><w/> <gloss><q>ударять</q></gloss></mentioned>, , — <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/> <w>Gras hauen</w> <gloss><q>косить траву</q></gloss></mentioned>. — Из осетинского (аланского) усвоено в западнокавказские языки: <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/> <w>šāmāg</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-crc"><lang/> <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(зап.) </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">(West) </note><w>čämäg</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="abq"><lang/> <w>čbəg</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/> <w>ā-čbəga</w> <gloss><q>коса</q></gloss></mentioned>. См. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cævyn"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>313, 336</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">A lexicalized past participle with the suffix -%iæg%i of the verb <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cævyn"/> ‘beat’, in fact “beating” and “cutting” tool. Cf. by the derivation <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/> <w>šalga</w> <gloss><q>scythe</q></gloss></mentioned> %bшорск%b. , literally “beating (tool)” from <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/> <w>šal-</w> <gloss><q>beat</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""><w/> <gloss><q>hit</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (<bibl><author>Dyrenkova</author><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Грамматика шорского языка, стр. 28</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">The grammar of Shor, p. 28</biblScope></bibl>); The development of the meaning ‘beat’ → ‘scythe’, like in German <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/> <w>hauen</w> <gloss><q>beat</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="de"><w/> <gloss><q>hit</q></gloss></mentioned>, , — <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/> <w>Gras hauen</w> <gloss><q>cut the grass</q></gloss></mentioned>. — The word was borrwed by West Caucasian languages from Ossetic:<mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/> <w>šāmāg</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-crc"><lang/> <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(зап.) </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">(West) </note><w>čämäg</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="abq"><lang/> <w>čbəg</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/> <w>ā-čbəga</w> <gloss><q>scythe</q></gloss></mentioned>. See <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cævyn"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>313, 336</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>